   Subscribe to the What's New at HHS Listserv

   1-24-2002
          HHS today released a new report showing significant improvements
          in the health of racial and ethnic minorities but also
          indicating that important disparities in health persist among
          different populations. Trends in Racial and Ethnic-Specific
          Rates for the Health Status Indicators: United States, 1990-1998
          presents national trends in racial- and ethnic-specific rates
          for 17 health status indicators during the 1990s.

   1-23-2002
          NIH's National Institute of Child Health and Human Development
          today released a new parenting booklet that incorporates three
          decades of research on effective parenting techniques and
          healthy child development. Adventures in Parenting: How
          Responding, Preventing, Monitoring, Mentoring, and Modeling Can
          Help You Be a Successful Parent highlights challenges that
          parents face in rearing happy and healthy children and suggests
          ways to become a more effective parent.

